title: Travis CI builds
message:
Travis CI builds

* Added .travis.yml that does the following:
  * creates an avd
  * starts an emulator
  * waits for the emulator to start
  * sets up the android sdk and the required components (with the needed license)
  * builds the source code
  * uploads the built artifact (apk) to github releases (only if a git tag was created for the same)

title: Using gradle build system.
message:
Using gradle build system.

The summary of import is listed below. Apart from that, the following changes were made:
* Using a customized gitignore file
* app/build.gradle updated to disable running proguard (needed for travis later)
* app/build.gradle update to disable aborting on error (needed for travis later)

In order to develop using this new build system:
* Download Android Studio here: https://developer.android.com/sdk/installing/studio.html
* Open the build.gradle file in Android Studio
* It will prompt you to "import" the project. This is a one-time step (unless you `git clean -fdx`). Press OK
* You are ready to go. Press Ctrl+R to build and run the app in the emulator

* AndroidManifest.xml => app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml
* libs/mongo-2.10.1.jar => app/libs/mongo-2.10.1.jar
* res/ => app/src/main/res/
* src/ => app/src/main/java/
